summary: The United States Senate successfully averted a potential government shutdown by passing a series of bills that allocate $1.2 trillion in funding. The motion has garnered attention as a sign of the deepening divide within the party, with some news outlets reporting it as a "surprise" or a "warning" to Johnson.
